description.p:
It was found that the compound of formula 9 has several remarkable advantages in comparison to other coupling reagents used in ixazomib chemistry:


1. It exhibits a minimal rate of epimerization during coupling; configuration on stereogenic centres is maintained;

2. It has very low toxicity and low sensitization potential; both TBTU and EDCI are very toxic compounds;

3. It can be removed after coupling reaction by simple washing with water. Known coupling agents and their reaction products often contaminate the product of coupling during isolation procedures which necessitates complicated purification processes;

4. It reacts at very mild conditions with high yield;

5. It has affordable price;

6. It is a stable product with easy handling and dosing, and is well soluble in common organic solvents, e.g. in ethyl acetate and/or in acetonitrile.
